              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cauliflower cheese and macaroni cheese are both British staples with long histories. Combining them into one tin is a practical piece of home-kitchen economy: two dishes for the effort of one, a more substantial result, and nothing wasted. It is firmly in the British tradition of stretching a cheese sauce as far as it will go.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
